      "variant": "Exon III 48-bp VNTR",
      "location_group": "East Asia",
      "summary": "East Asian cohorts are often described as having relatively more 2-repeat alleles and comparatively fewer 7-repeat alleles, so some studies treat 2R as the functionally analogous risk-focused allele in these populations.",
